Retrieve data from Confluence: You will need to use Confluence's API to retrieve the pages you want to use as data for your GPT model. You can use the Confluence REST API to retrieve the pages in a specific space or search for pages based on a specific keyword.

Preprocess the data: Once you have retrieved the pages from Confluence, you will need to preprocess the data to prepare it for training the GPT model. This may involve cleaning up the text, removing any unwanted characters, and breaking the text into smaller chunks.

Train the GPT model: There are several libraries available for training GPT models, such as Hugging Face's Transformers or OpenAI's GPT-3 API. You will need to provide the preprocessed data to the GPT model and specify the model's hyperparameters and training parameters.

Fine-tune the GPT model: Depending on the specific use case, you may want to fine-tune the GPT model with additional data or adjust the model's hyperparameters. This can help improve the model's performance on the specific task you are using it for.